<TEXT>
coast guardsmen in the florida keys have worked 
for cocaine smugglers selling them agents codes and disabling 
patrol boats according to a report broadcast sunday 
when they raided smugglers homes federal authorities found 
records of secret radio frequencies patrol schedules and codes 
used in radio transmissions for every law enforcement agency in the 
florida keys nbcs expose show reported 
the report made no mention of when the alleged corruption 
occurred however lt cmdr jeff karonis spokesman for the coast 
guards southeastern district based in miami told the associated 
press that the coast guard had put an end to the alleged conspiracy 
back in 1988 
the coast guard people involved were brought to justice and 
are in jail right now the system works and theyre paying for 
it karonis said after viewing the broadcast sunday 
the nbc report cited unidentified federal authorities and tom 
cash an official with the us drug enforcement administration in 
miami 
federal authorities probing the relationship between smugglers 
and coast guardsmen named the case operation tempest 
at least 15 guardsmen assigned to the islamorada station worked 
for or with the smugglers they were assigned to catch nbc reported 
admiral paul yost coast guard commandant said he was unaware 
of any federal investigation of cocaine involvement in the coast 
guard nbc said 
weve got almost no drug corruption one or two isolated 
cases yost said 
four islamorada guardsmen who crewed a highspeed boat intended 
to intercept smugglers are in jail for taking cocaine from the 
smugglers nbc said 
art sola commander of the crew that allegedly stole cocaine 
from smugglers for themselves told nbc he and his fellow guardsmen 
decided one afternoon to steal a kilogram of cocaine from a load 
they found floating in the atlantic ocean 15 miles offshore 
the cocaine was worth as much as 16000 about the same as the 
guardsmens salary 
its easy its very easy its a lifestyle down there 
everybody knows somebody whos involved in drugs or smuggling its 
very easy to get hooked on sola said in an interview in jail 
another guardsman bobby gosnell got caught up in drug 
smuggling but wound up murdered nbc said after he left the coast 
guard gosnell bought a 500000 home complete with an airstrip 
the station said 
gosnell was shot in the chest in a dispute over whether he 
should cooperate with the federal investigation nbc said 
</TEXT>
