<TEXT>
a pleasure boat struck the underpinning 
of a highway bridge saturday night on the rainswollen missouri 
river slightly injuring 22 passengers sent sprawling across decks 
by the impact 
the doubledecked boat the spirit of st charles struck a 
bridge pillar as it tried to turn downstream said ray kemp public 
affairs officer for the st charles county ambulance service 
there was a lot of screaming because the impact was pretty 
strong he said a little girl fell down some stairs but she 
wasnt seriously hurt 
the injured were treated at st joseph health center said 
barbara wussler the centers community relations director they 
were treated for minor injuries she said 
the boat carrying 217 passengers returned to a shore of the 
river which crested friday night at st charles 10 feet over its 
25foot flood stage 
the extent of damage to the boat was not immediately determined 
st charles is about 20 miles west of st louis 
