<TEXT>
several thousand riot police firing 
tear gas stormed a university campus sunday to break up an 
antigovernment rally by 5000 students and workers 
radical students and workers wielding metal pipes rocks and 
firebombs battled police amid a thick fog of tear gas on the campus 
of chosun university 
elsewhere in this provincial city more than 10000 students 
rallied at the national chonnam university burning a giant us 
flag and shouting insults at thousands of riot police outside the 
campus 
police officials said a student from seoul died in a hospital 
saturday of massive head injuries suffered after he jumped off a 
speeding train on the outskirts of kwangju 
police said shin jangho21 a sophomore at daeyu vocational 
college in seoul was among several hundred students who jumped to 
avoid being arrested at the kwangju railway station police checked 
identities of all students arriving in kwangju by train car and 
bus in an effort to prevent outsiders from joining the protesters 
at a downtown hospital where shins body was kept about 500 
students armed with steel pipes and firebombs stood guard police 
officials expressed concern the death might further radicalize the 
students 
at chosun university about 2500 riot police supported by four 
armored vans firing hundreds of volleys of tear gas stormed the 
campus as about 5000 workers and students were starting an 
antigovernment rally 
down with president roh taewoo protesters shouted as 
they dashed through thick clouds of tear gas to charge the police 
lines 
about 300 protesters barricaded themselved on the roofs of 
several school buildings pelting police with rocks and firebombs 
about a dozen police officers were injured and evacuated some 
women protesters overcome by the tear gas were carried into 
campus buildings by colleagues 
at chonnam university about 25000 students held a rally 
overnight during which they demanded the ouster of roh and us 
troops based in korea yankee go home students screamed 
jabbing their hands in the air 
the students planned to hold a mass antigovernment rally sunday 
in central kwangju with dissident groups police said the rally 
would be illegal and they planned to block it 
early saturday about 3500 police supported by armored teargas 
vans surrounded the chonnam campus and searched all visitors about 
230 students were arrested police said 
but as news of the students death spread the riot police 
withdrew apparently to avoid provoking protesters 
the number of students at the school increased sharply after the 
police departed 
students used tires school desks chairs and broken furniture 
to erect 10 to 12foothigh barricades at the universitys three 
gates more than 500 students armed with 3footlong metal pipes 
stood guard inside each one 
our nation has no hope until president roh taewoo and the 
united states are ousted student leader song gapsuk told a 
rally 
song a fugitive being sought by police for instigating violent 
protests said the us military presence in south korea is a major 
obstacle to seouls unification with communist north korea the 
crowd applauded and cheered wildly 
about 43000 us troops are stationed in south korea 
in downtown kwangju several groups of 50 to 100 students hurled 
rocks and firebombs at riot police in sporadic clashes during the 
day police dispersed them with tear gas 
about 7000 people rioted in the streets of this city on friday 
the 10th anniversary of a prodemocracy revolt that was crushed by 
the military at least 200 civilians were killed in the 10day 
uprising the worst in modern korean history 
fridays protesters attacked police with rocks and firebombs and 
demanded the ouster of roh 
the anniversary also was marked by protests in more than a dozen 
other cities and police said about 5300 people were arrested 
police said all but 481 of the 4325 arrested in seoul had been 
released they said 123 people were arrested in kwangju and that at 
least were 20 injured 
antius and antigovernment sentiment is strong in kwangju a 
city of more than 1 million people 156 miles south of seoul many 
citizens feel the united states stood by and condoned the bloody 
suppression in 1980 washington repeatedly has denied the charges 
the us cultural center in the city was forced to close last 
year after it was attacked by radicals 28 times since the early 
1980s 
