<TEXT>
a marine corps helicopter crashed 
during a training flight saturday killing one of six crew members 
officials said 
the ch53d helicopter had mechanical difficulty and crashed 
about 15 miles south of salton sea said a statement from the 3rd 
marine aircraft wing headquarters at el toro marine corps air 
station 
the conditions of the five survivors were not immediately 
available the names of all six crew members were withheld pending 
notification of relatives 
the cause of the crash was under investigation 
the ch53d or delta model is known as the sea stallion it 
is powered by two engines 
in 1985 17 marines were lost at sea and presumed dead when a 
sea stallion crashed off the southern coast of japan in 1987 four 
marines survived a fiery crash of a sea stallion in the arizona 
desert 
the helicopter was based at the tustin station in orange county 
and was attached to marine heavy helicopter squadron 363 
salton city is about 55 miles southeast of los angeles 
