<TEXT>
a major earthquake rocked southern sudan 
early sunday near the wartorn regions largest city which is 
crammed with refugees 
there were no immediate reports of damage or injuries but 
experts said widespread destruction was virtually certain given the 
magnitude of the quake 
scientists said the quakes epicenter was only 60 miles 
northeast of the city of juba whose normal population of 125000 
has more than doubled with people fleeing the countrys civil war 
the epicenter was near the nile river about 700 miles south of 
khartoum the capital of the african country 
most of southern sudan is controlled by the rebel sudan peoples 
liberation army western relief workers are posted in juba and 
other major cities still controlled by the government 
the quake registering 75 on the richter scale occurred at 
422 am said geologist rashad m kebeasy president of egypts 
national research institute of astronomy and geophysics 
the quake was registered by egypts two principal seismic 
monitoring stations kebeasy said 
pat jorgenson a spokeswoman for the us geological survey in 
menlo park calif reported identical data 
its such a big quake that the monitoring stations are 
saturated with data so its difficult to get everything precise 
right now kebeasy said this is an extremely dangerous 
earthquake it is the first time that such a quake has struck this 
area 
kebeasy an expert on earthquakes in northeast africa said the 
epicenter lies just west of the great african rift an earthquake 
zone stretching 4000 miles from mozambique through the red sea to 
lebanon 
its proximity to the rift accounts for the quakes ferocity 
kebeasy said 
warn people to beware he said we can expect large and 
very dangerous aftershocks for the next two days he said 
the sudan peoples liberation army launched its rebellion in 
1983 demanding greater autonomy and economic reforms for the 
countrys three southern provinces whose population is mostly 
animist or christian the rest of the country is predominantly 
moslem 
hundreds of thousands of people mainly civilians have died 
either from the fighting or the famine it has caused 
the richter scale is a gauge of the energy released by an 
earthquake as measured by the ground motion recorded on a 
seismograph 
every increase of one number say from magnitude 55 to 
magnitude 65 means that the ground motion is 10 times greater 
magnitude 7 is considered a major earthquake capable of 
widespread heavy damage magnitude 8 is a great earthquake 
capable of tremendous damage the october 17 1989 earthquake near 
san francisco measured 71 on the richter scale 
</TEXT>
