the return of wolves running wild through 
yellowstone national park would add to the enjoyment of tourists 
and restore a missing link in the parks ecosystem experts say 
but ranchers fearful of livestock losses oppose reintroducing 
the predators 81000 of which were killed between 1883 and 1918 in 
