<TEXT>
nasa engineers captured the first 
light photograph sunday of the hubble space telescope and a 
scientist said the experts were pleased as punch with the 
spectacular image 
a camera on the telescope clicked its shutter twice beginning at 
1113 am edt and the images were relayed to the ground more than 
two hours later giving astronomers their first glimpses of the 
view from the 15 billion telescope 
its quite an image fantastic james westphal the 
principal scientist for the camera used in the first photo 
exercise said as one the photos was displayed on a tv screen 
we are just as pleased as punch at this point westphal 
said our image is significantly better than we were concerned 
that it might be 
westphal said the hubble image revealed a double star that was 
previously unseen in groundbased photographs taken at an 
observatory in chile 
we didnt know it was a double star said westphal noting 
that he had expected the first image to be an engineering test 
but because of the clarity of the image he said boy we could 
get lots of science out of this right now 
the quality of the photo was a boost for national aeronautics 
and space administration officials who have gone through an 
unexpectedly troubled checkout and testing period with the costly 
telescope which is in orbit 381 miles above earth 
the target for hubbles first image was a star cluster called 
theta carina a group of objects about 1260 light years from 
earth the telescope took two exposures one for a single second 
and another lasting 30 seconds 
westphal said the 30second exposure was chosen for analysis 
because it gave better detail 
engineers manipulated the images while people watched on 
television and it took them over an hour to change the raw 
electronic data from hubble into a photograph on a tv screen 
nobody has ever done this before so we had to learn how 
westphal said the technical challenge now is to get the 
telescope in even sharper focus 
the scientists said that eventually they expect to get 
photographs at least seven times sharper than the one released 
sunday 
the image came down as four separate parts of the same photo 
engineers then used computer instructions to enhance the quality of 
each point of light the initial look at the photo showed very 
faint points of light on a gray field 
after manipulation the stars were brightened the background 
was darkened and the double star could be seen easily 
theta carina is part of a constellation called carina a word 
that means ships keel that is visible from the ground only in 
the southern hemisphere the star cluster is identified in the new 
general catalogue of stars as 3532 and is thought to be 3 billion 
years old its distance from earth is about 7400000000000000 
miles 
nasa officials said the first light photo is an important 
engineering milestone for the hubble checkout 
engineers have spent a month attempting to align and focus the 
instruments of hubble they have had to overcome computer problems 
a fouled antenna a programing error that resulted from an ordinary 
math mistake and an unexplained wobble that still is unresolved 
the checkout said be stull of lockheed missiles and space 
co the prime nasa contractor for the telescope has been a 
little more stressful and challenging that we expected 
we certainly expected some difficulties but we didnt expect 
the severity and the number that we got he told the washington 
post 
the telescope will undergo another seven months or so of intense 
checkout and testing before the fulltime programs of scientific 
study begin 
officials said long breakin periods are not unusual for robot 
spacecraft and the testing is even more difficult because of the 
precise demands of hubble the most powerful astronomical 
observatory ever put into orbit 
hubble by working from an orbit above the obscuring effects of 
the earths atmosphere will able to look at stars in the far 
reaches of the universe perhaps to point 14 billion light years 
from earth 
with its 945inchdiameter mirror and powerful lightamplifying 
and focusing equipment the orbiting telescope is expected to 
eventually take photos of stars that are 25 times fainter than the 
dimmest object visible from earth the best hubble pictures are 
expected to have 10 times the clarity of photos taken by the most 
powerful groundbased telescopes 
to accomplish this the telescope is designed to hold so steady 
that its motion in any direction would be less than the thickness 
of a sheet of paper its pointing system is so accurate that if it 
was mounted atop the washington monument with a laser gun it could 
hold a steady light beam on a dime atop the empire state building 
in new york city 
hubble was carried into space last month by space shuttle 
discovery on april 25 it was plucked from the shuttles cargo bay 
and left to orbit on its own 381 miles above the earth 
