<TEXT>
arab states and groups expressed outrage 
sunday over the killings of seven unarmed palestinian laborers by 
an israeli civilian and called for renewed protests in the 
israelioccupied territories 
the shooting sunday blamed on an israeli who had been 
dishonorably discharged from the army set off riots in the 
israelioccupied territories that left seven other palestinians 
dead and hundreds injured 
sunday was one of the most violent days since the start of the 
intefadah the palestinian uprising that broke out in december 1987 
against israeli military rule in the west bank and the gaza strip 
israeli officials themselves condemned the attack which one 
general called a tragic act by a deranged individual but many 
arab officials said it represented a pattern of violence against 
palestinians 
palestine liberation organization chief yasser arafat called on 
palestinians in the occupied territories to stage protests in 
every village every city and every camp of the israelioccupied 
territory 
the plo chief also urged international intervention to protect 
palestinians against the crimes of the israeli army and 
colonialists referring to jewish settlers in the territories 
wafa the plo news agency said the plo made a formal protest to 
the united states on sunday over the incident saying it held 
washington responsible for israeli genocide operations against 
palestinians the plos permanent representative to tunisia hakam 
balaoui submitted the protest note to the us embassy in tunis 
in jordan prime minister mudar badran called the shootings a 
criminal act which is also denounced by all arabs all moslems 
and all the people of the world who have a live conscience 
roughly half of jordans 31 million people come from 
palestinian families who fled or were forced out of their homeland 
during the 1948 and 1967 arabisraeli wars 
in lebanon shiite moslem militia chieftain nabih berri who is 
also a government minister condemned the attack as a horrifying 
massacre and called in a statement for a nationwide protest 
strike wednesday 
egypt on sunday expressed deep sorrow over the killings 
which it said reflected the prevailing climate in israel and in 
israelioccupied arab territories 
this painful incident no doubt affirms once more the 
importance of overcoming all obstacles hindering the peace 
process foreign minister esmat abdelmeguid told reporters 
clovis maksoud the ambassador to the united states and the 
united nations from the league of arab states accused israel of 
have a deliberate plan to expedite through escalating violence 
its strategy to crush the uprising 
