police on sunday opened fire 
on black demonstrators returning from a meeting where they decided 
to end a boycott of whiteowned businesses three people were 
reported killed and 12 wounded 
the incident began after thousands of blacks held the meeting in 
the thabong township outside the mining town of welkom 150 miles 
southwest of johannesburg the boycott they decided to end was 11 
days old 
