<TEXT>
czechoslovakia on sunday joined four 
other european nations in the first regional cooperation group to 
unite nato warsaw pact and neutral nations 
the other members of the group are austria italy yugoslavia 
and hungary 
representatives of the five nations met in vienna on sunday to 
discuss ways of furthering cooperation in transport 
communications the environment culture and small businesses 
a senior foreign ministry official from hungary and the foreign 
ministers of the other nations took part in the discussions 
the organization grew out of cooperation between border regions 
of italy yugoslavia austria and hungary that began 11 years ago 
it is the only regional cooperation organization to unite 
neutral nations with countries from the wests north atlantic 
treaty organization and the sovietled warsaw pact 
the four nations decided to boost cooperation last fall just 
before a peaceful revolution in czechoslovakia toppled the 
communists and brought a prodemocracy government headed by former 
dissidents to power 
the decision to admit czechoslovakia was taken in april members 
of the group said say romania and bulgaria have also applied to 
join 
italian foreign minister gianni de michelis said at a news 
conference that one aim of the organization is to ensure that 
western europe does not become preoccupied with questions posed by 
germanys reunification at the expense of other regions 
he said the five nations hope to be among the first to apply for 
investment grants to the new bank for european development and 
cooperation formally founded in paris on saturday 
the five also intend to present to a forthcoming 35nation 
conference in copenhagen denmark on human rights proposals on 
minority rights designed to defuse potential ethnic conflicts 
particularly those in eastern europe de michelis said 
during an hourlong televised discussion the five officials each 
stressed the importance of the group as a way to bring together 
organizations with diverse affiliations but common pasts and 
interests 
yugoslavia is nonaligned and in transition between communism and 
democracy czechoslovakia and hungary moving swiftly toward 
westernstyle democracy are still members of the sovietled warsaw 
pact and comecon austria is a neutral member of the european free 
trade association and italy is in nato and the european community 
