<TEXT>
marriott corp said it still is considering 
proposals to sell its family restaurant business but is not 
negotiating a sale with sizzler restaurants international inc 
marriott said in a statement saturday that numerous parties 
including sizzler have expressed interest in the restaurants and 
that it is evaluating their proposals 
but the company said it was not in negotiations with sizzler 
contrary to public statements made by sizzler 
no decision to negotiate with any single party has been 
made the statement said 
marriott officials announced in december their intention to 
withdraw from the family restaurant business as part of a corporate 
restructuring aimed at focusing the companys assets 
based in washington dc marriott currently operates over 400 
restaurants including those under the names of bobs big boy and 
howard johnsons 
