the average price of a gallon of gasoline at 
the nations pumps rose 24 cents in the past two weeks a survey 
showed 
the price was 11605 cents a gallon in the lundberg survey for 
the period ended may 18 up 24 cents from the average in the 
previous survey may 4 industry analyst trilby lundberg said sunday 
the average includes regular unleaded premium unleaded and 
regular leaded gasoline and all taxes lundberg surveys 13000 
stations nationwide 
selfserve prices per gallon were regular unleaded 10447 
cents premium unleaded 12165 cents regular leaded 10391 cents 
fullserve prices were regular unleaded 13098 premium unleaded 
14451 regular leaded 12893 
